                        <ce:para>Recently, a method for explaining the model's decision for an instance was introduced by Robnik-Šikonja and Kononenko. It is a rare example of a model-independent explanation method. In this paper we make a step towards formalization of the model-independent explanation methods by defining the criteria and a testing environment for such methods. We extensively test the aforementioned method and its variations. The results confirm some of the qualities of the original method as well as expose several of its shortcomings. We propose a new method, based on attribute interactions, that overcomes the shortcomings of the original method and serves as a theoretical framework for further work. © 2008 Springer-Verlag Berlin Heidelberg.</ce:para>
